        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 5 at 8:28PM CDT until July 5 at 9:00PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 827 PM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 4 miles west of Dalhart to 7 miles northwest of
Romero, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile homes,
roofs, and outbuildings. Hail damage to vehicles is
expected.

Locations impacted include...
Dalhart and Romero.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading
killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to
be struck by lightning.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
